name: Southeastern High Speed Extended
location: Dartford - Ashford International and London St. Pancras - Faversham

routeFacts.name: Southeastern High Speed Extended
routeFacts.description: Southeastern High Speed Extended is a route featured in the base game of Train Sim World 3. It is an extended version of the Southeastern High Speed route, featuring extensions from Ebbsfleet to Ashford, and from Gravesend to Dartford, extending the total length of the route to 89 miles. Also included are the BR Class 66 freight locomotive, and the BR Class 465 EMU, which was previously featured as a locomotive add-on for the original Southeastern High Speed route. The extended version of Southeastern High Speed in TSW3 includes the previous 100 collectibles from the TSW2 with at least a few dozen extra collectibles to find. This map shows all known collectibles.
routeInfo: There are two main components to the extended Southeastern High Speed route - High Speed One running from LondonSt Pancras to Ashford International via Stratford and Ebbsfleet, and the North Kent/Catham Main Lines from Dartford to Faversham, via Gravesend and Catham, with two different parts of the route connecting at Ebbsfleet. High Speed One is Britain's only high speed railway, with domestic services operated by the BR Class 395 reaching speeds of up to 140 mph. Services on this route operate using overhead electrification and TVM signalling. The slower conventional route from Dartford to Faversham operates commuter services using third rail and traditional signalling.
